WEBVTT

00:00.709 --> 00:02.794
♪ ♪

00:07.006 --> 00:09.050
(mouthing)

00:12.721 --> 00:14.764
(camera shutter clicking)

00:16.975 --> 00:20.562
DIRECTOR:
Beautiful, Fiji. You're a star.

00:22.897 --> 00:26.443
Now you're slowly coming out
of your shell.

00:26.526 --> 00:29.279
Move your arms
a little bit more.

00:29.362 --> 00:31.197
Incredible!

00:31.281 --> 00:32.782
Yes!

00:32.866 --> 00:35.577
Now look down.

00:35.660 --> 00:37.996
And then look right into
the barrel of the camera,

00:38.079 --> 00:40.957
but this time,
you're in the water.

00:41.040 --> 00:42.625
You're floating in the water.

00:42.709 --> 00:44.169
You're a beautiful octopus.

00:44.252 --> 00:46.337
Use your tentacles.

00:46.880 --> 00:48.923
You're about to feed

00:49.007 --> 00:50.300
on your prey.

00:50.383 --> 00:53.636
You've got fire in your belly.

00:53.720 --> 00:54.179
You're looking

00:54.262 --> 00:56.681
at your prey from above,

00:56.765 --> 00:59.267
and you're just trying
to imagine

00:59.350 --> 01:03.813
who you're about to devour.

01:03.897 --> 01:04.772
Perfect!

01:04.855 --> 01:08.985
-You're gorgeous. Okay, cut!
-(applause)

01:09.068 --> 01:11.488
(bell rings)

01:11.571 --> 01:13.615
(cheering, whooping)

01:16.868 --> 01:18.787
DIRECTOR:
Great job, Fiji.

01:18.870 --> 01:21.956
{\an5}-(cheering)
-This video's gonna
break the Internet.

01:22.040 --> 01:25.043
It was such a pleasure
working for you.

01:30.423 --> 01:32.842
{\an5}JENNIFER:
Fiji, the song is incredible,
and that video

01:32.926 --> 01:35.011
is clearly gonna be a huge hit.
You must be so excited

01:35.094 --> 01:36.930
to share it with the world.

01:38.097 --> 01:40.683
Anyway,
I wanted to say thank you

01:40.767 --> 01:42.560
for letting me
follow you around today.

01:42.644 --> 01:44.187
The article
should be out next month.

01:44.270 --> 01:46.189
Cool.

01:46.272 --> 01:48.817
Can't wait to see
what you do next.

01:48.900 --> 01:51.820
{\an5}-Yeah, it's gonna be
a really big hit.
-(Jennifer chuckles)

01:51.903 --> 01:54.489
SANTINO:
Car's out here, Miss Fiji.

01:55.907 --> 01:59.536
I think I'm gonna walk today,
Santino.

02:04.082 --> 02:06.084
(indistinct chatter)

02:09.253 --> 02:11.172
(dog barking)

02:11.256 --> 02:13.258
(siren wailing)

02:15.468 --> 02:17.470
(guitar playing)

02:33.361 --> 02:35.405
-Nice song.
-JASMINE: Thanks.

02:39.826 --> 02:41.202
Hey.

02:41.286 --> 02:43.162
You, uh...

02:43.246 --> 02:46.082
-Yeah, it's me. It's me.
-Holy shit! (laughs)

02:47.125 --> 02:49.002
I love your music.

02:49.085 --> 02:50.712
Thanks.

02:52.130 --> 02:55.049
So, what do you want?

02:55.133 --> 02:56.926
Huh? What do I want?

02:57.010 --> 02:59.721
What do you want? With all this?

03:00.722 --> 03:02.682
(chuckles softly)

03:02.765 --> 03:05.143
Hell, I-I guess
I want what you have.

03:15.737 --> 03:17.655
What do I have?

03:17.739 --> 03:19.282
WOMAN:
Oh, my God!

03:19.365 --> 03:22.118
It's Fiji!
It's Fiji, everyone!

03:22.201 --> 03:24.579
I love you!

03:24.662 --> 03:27.290
-Can I get a selfie?
-MAN: Fiji!

03:27.373 --> 03:29.083
-Oh, my God.
-MAN: Fiji, can I get a selfie?

03:29.167 --> 03:30.919
-Oh, my God.
-You don't understand.

03:31.002 --> 03:33.796
{\an5}-Your music has changed my life.
I-I can't...
-Fiji, Fiji!

03:33.880 --> 03:35.798
(overlapping fan chatter)

03:35.882 --> 03:37.800
(applause)

03:37.884 --> 03:39.344
(phone camera shutters clicking)

03:39.427 --> 03:41.346
♪ ♪

03:41.429 --> 03:43.473
(overlapping fan chatter)

03:48.603 --> 03:52.231
-(all gasp)
-(screaming)

03:52.315 --> 03:53.983
(alarmed shouting, screaming)

03:59.280 --> 04:01.324
(siren wails)

04:06.579 --> 04:08.623
(indistinct conversation)

04:14.253 --> 04:15.838
{\an5}ZARA:
How long is this gonna
keep going on?

04:15.922 --> 04:18.007
How-how long are you gonna
keep encouraging her?

04:18.091 --> 04:19.676
DELANCEY:
Look, it's hard, Zara. Eh...

04:19.759 --> 04:21.344
You're not a parent.

04:21.427 --> 04:22.887
(Zara scoffs)

04:22.971 --> 04:24.639
(water running)

04:24.722 --> 04:26.349
{\an5}ZARA:
Well, you know
what she did today?

04:26.432 --> 04:30.353
She spent all day singing
on the street like a bum,

04:30.436 --> 04:32.855
begging for change.

04:32.939 --> 04:34.440
DELANCEY:
Your Uncle Vin

04:34.524 --> 04:36.985
{\an5}-said he had
a receptionist position open.
-Mm.

04:37.068 --> 04:40.863
But I can't just
make her call him.

04:40.947 --> 04:43.074
I-I'm just trying to be
supportive.

04:43.157 --> 04:46.035
{\an5}ZARA:
Right. Well, if you really want
to be supportive,

04:46.119 --> 04:47.870
you should probably stop
encouraging

04:47.954 --> 04:49.831
this ridiculous dream of hers.

04:49.914 --> 04:52.250
I mean, it's just...
It's never going to happen.

04:52.333 --> 04:54.377
(keys slam loudly)

04:57.130 --> 04:59.340
-Hey, Jas. Uh...
-Hey, sweetheart.

04:59.424 --> 05:02.510
{\an5}-If you're hungry,
I'm making curry.
-(door shuts)

05:02.593 --> 05:04.595
♪ ♪

05:24.574 --> 05:26.576
♪ ♪

05:34.542 --> 05:36.586
(indistinct chatter)

05:40.548 --> 05:42.592
(horn honks)

06:01.819 --> 06:03.821
♪ ♪

06:15.375 --> 06:18.753
♪<i> She dances for me</i> ♪

06:18.836 --> 06:22.715
♪<i> All that is she I long to be</i> ♪

06:28.888 --> 06:32.475
♪<i> They silence her voice,</i>
<i>but I hear her sway</i> ♪

06:32.558 --> 06:36.854
♪<i> Within the sea</i>
<i>of their shame</i> ♪

06:40.399 --> 06:43.152
♪<i> Fire lady, all you are</i> ♪

06:43.236 --> 06:46.989
{\an5}-♪<i> What you battle</i>
<i>in your heart</i> ♪
-(applause)

06:47.073 --> 06:49.283
♪<i> Has left me scarred.</i> ♪

06:59.418 --> 07:01.462
(all cheering, whooping)

07:12.098 --> 07:15.560
(laughs)

07:15.643 --> 07:18.479
{\an5}NARRATOR:
Jasmine Delancey
has spent her entire life

07:18.563 --> 07:20.648
in search of one thing:

07:20.731 --> 07:22.817
applause.

07:22.900 --> 07:25.361
Now that she's found it,
it's given her

07:25.444 --> 07:27.363
a new sense of meaning.

07:27.446 --> 07:29.198
But what, exactly, is the value

07:29.282 --> 07:33.327
of an ovation so loud
it drowns out the performance?

07:33.411 --> 07:36.414
Jasmine's about to find out
here...

07:36.497 --> 07:39.417
in The Twilight Zone.

07:39.500 --> 07:40.459
<i>(The Twilight Zone</i> theme
playing)

07:40.543 --> 07:42.545
<i>You're traveling</i>
<i>through another dimension,</i>

07:42.628 --> 07:46.090
<i>a dimension not only of</i>
<i>sight and sound but of mind.</i>

07:46.174 --> 07:48.968
<i>It is the middle ground</i>
<i>between light and shadow,</i>

07:49.051 --> 07:51.637
<i>between science</i>
<i>and superstition.</i>

07:51.721 --> 07:54.599
{\an8}<i>And it lies between</i>
<i>the pit of one's fears</i>

07:54.682 --> 07:57.393
{\an8}<i>and the summit</i>
<i>of one's knowledge.</i>

07:57.476 --> 08:00.897
<i>You are now traveling through</i>
<i>a dimension of imagination.</i>

08:00.980 --> 08:04.901
<i>You've just crossed over</i>
<i>into The Twilight Zone.</i>

08:09.947 --> 08:10.865
JASMINE:
Thank you so much.

08:10.948 --> 08:12.700
♪ ♪

08:12.783 --> 08:14.285
Pardon me, ladies.

08:14.368 --> 08:16.412
Hi, how are you? Hi.
Excuse me.

08:20.166 --> 08:23.920
{\an8}Uh, let me just real quickly
grab my jaw... (chuckles)

08:24.003 --> 08:25.129
{\an8}...off the floor.

08:25.213 --> 08:27.423
{\an8}-(laughs)
-You are <i> good.</i>

08:27.506 --> 08:29.425
{\an8}-Really?
-Yeah.

08:29.508 --> 08:31.385
{\an8}-Think so?
-I know so.

08:33.471 --> 08:34.931
{\an8}You know who I am, right?

08:35.014 --> 08:36.640
{\an8}-Yeah.
-Yeah?

08:36.724 --> 08:38.476
{\an8}You're that guy
that hosts that show.

08:38.558 --> 08:42.395
{\an8}(laughs):
Oh! Undersell it.

08:42.480 --> 08:44.649
{\an8}<i>Ovation with J.J. Malloy.</i>

08:44.732 --> 08:46.901
{\an8}The highest rated show
on broadcast television.

08:46.984 --> 08:50.571
{\an8}-My dad watches it.
-Everybody's dad watches it.

08:52.531 --> 08:54.408
{\an8}You know I could
make you a star, right?

08:55.409 --> 08:56.869
{\an8}Huh?

08:57.870 --> 09:00.456
{\an8}What's your name?

09:00.539 --> 09:03.918
{\an8}<i>ANNOUNCER (on TV):</i>
<i>Get ready for an all-new season</i>
<i>of</i> Ovation,

09:04.001 --> 09:06.629
{\an8}<i>where your applause</i>
<i>equals stardom.</i>

09:06.712 --> 09:08.798
{\an8}Join your host, J.J. Malloy...

09:08.881 --> 09:11.175
{\an8}<i>MALLOY: Did you miss me,</i>
<i>you guys? I missed you.</i>

09:11.259 --> 09:14.428
{\an8}<i>ANNOUNCER:</i>
<i>...as he introduces you</i>
<i>to this year's wannabes</i>

09:14.512 --> 09:16.138
{\an8}<i>and will-never-bes.</i>

09:16.222 --> 09:17.640
{\an8}<i>-If you want to make it...</i>
-(door closes)

09:17.723 --> 09:19.141
{\an8}<i>...you can't fake it.</i>

09:19.225 --> 09:21.936
{\an8}<i>It takes real talent</i>
<i>to survive.</i>

09:22.019 --> 09:24.146
{\an8}You know that corny-ass dude
J.J. Malloy from <i> Ovation?</i>

09:24.230 --> 09:26.315
{\an8}Oh, yeah, the weirdo
with the mustache?

09:26.399 --> 09:27.858
{\an8}Hands me his card, tells me

09:27.942 --> 09:29.819
{\an8}-he wants me to come
on the show. Mm-hmm.
-What? Really?

09:29.902 --> 09:31.654
{\an8}I don't know what happened,
but something shifted,

09:31.737 --> 09:33.614
{\an8}and the universe was like,
"Hi, Jasmine."

09:33.698 --> 09:34.824
{\an8}<i>Ovation?</i>

09:34.907 --> 09:37.493
{\an8}I know,<i> Ovation</i> is cheesy, but

09:37.576 --> 09:39.120
{\an8}auditions are tomorrow.
You got to come.

09:39.203 --> 09:40.162
{\an8}Oh, tomorrow?
I don't think I can.

09:40.246 --> 09:41.330
{\an8}-I have to work.
-Uh-uh, Z.

09:41.414 --> 09:42.748
{\an8}I mean, I need you there.

09:42.832 --> 09:44.000
{\an8}What are you talking about?
Just find

09:44.083 --> 09:46.168
{\an8}-a sub or something.
-It's cardiac surgery.

09:46.252 --> 09:49.505
{\an8}I don't exactly have an
understudy waiting in the wings.

09:49.588 --> 09:52.133
{\an8}Yeah. No, you're right.

09:52.216 --> 09:55.469
{\an8}Well, if I make it
to the finals next week,

09:55.553 --> 09:56.637
{\an8}can you please come?

09:56.721 --> 09:59.849
{\an8}"If"? How about <i> when</i> you make it
to the finals?

09:59.932 --> 10:01.475
{\an8}And when you win
this whole thing,

10:01.559 --> 10:03.019
{\an8}you can finally start
paying me rent.

10:03.102 --> 10:05.563
{\an8}-I'll pay you rent.
-Halle-fucking-lujah.

10:05.646 --> 10:08.649
{\an8}I'll buy you a car.
What kind of car you want? Hmm?

10:08.733 --> 10:10.443
{\an8}Right now I want
more of my carrots back.

10:10.526 --> 10:13.529
{\an8}-(laughs)
-You ate all my carrots.

10:13.612 --> 10:15.197
{\an8}(quietly):
<i>Ovation.</i>

10:15.281 --> 10:17.533
{\an8}<i>ANNOUNCER:</i>
<i>Welcome to Studio 5.</i>

10:17.616 --> 10:19.535
{\an8}<i>Before you can sing</i>
<i>for America,</i>

10:19.618 --> 10:24.206
{\an8}<i>you have to get through our</i>
<i>panel of industry tastemakers.</i>

10:24.290 --> 10:25.875
{\an8}♪<i> What is havin' faith,</i>
<i>if you don't exercise it?</i> ♪

10:25.958 --> 10:27.043
{\an8}DIRECTOR:
And ready, camera one?

10:27.126 --> 10:28.252
{\an8}♪<i> I feel your pain</i> ♪

10:28.336 --> 10:29.670
{\an8}D.P.:
Roger.

10:29.754 --> 10:31.589
{\an8}♪<i> But I need you to change.</i> ♪

10:31.672 --> 10:33.799
{\an8}(drumroll)

10:36.635 --> 10:38.137
{\an8}(scattered applause)

10:42.099 --> 10:43.559
{\an8}-Ooh.
<i>-(Price Is Right</i> horn plays)

10:43.642 --> 10:45.227
{\an8}I liked it,

10:45.311 --> 10:47.938
{\an8}Davood, but the Sound-O-Meter
doesn't lie.

10:48.022 --> 10:50.149
{\an8}-So sorry.
Better luck next time.
-(warbling horn)

10:50.232 --> 10:53.277
{\an8}And now, our next contestant
I found when I was

10:53.361 --> 10:56.238
{\an8}on my way to get some Thai food.

10:56.322 --> 10:58.699
{\an8}But I ended up getting
something much spicier.

10:58.783 --> 11:00.576
{\an8}Jasmine Delancey.

11:00.659 --> 11:02.703
{\an8}♪ ♪

11:09.794 --> 11:12.421
{\an8}-DIRECTOR: Okay, camera three.
-D.P.: Copy that.

11:12.505 --> 11:14.507
{\an8}-(coughing)
-(yawning)

11:17.802 --> 11:19.720
{\an8}-So do I just start singing?
-Yeah.

11:19.804 --> 11:22.640
{\an8}-Like, now?
-That's the idea. Yeah.
That'd be great.

11:24.642 --> 11:26.477
{\an8}(clears throat)

11:26.560 --> 11:28.604
{\an8}-Jasmine Delancey.
-(exhales)

11:31.524 --> 11:33.526
(guitar playing)

11:45.037 --> 11:48.624
♪<i> She dances for me</i> ♪

11:48.707 --> 11:52.711
♪<i> All that is she I long to be</i> ♪

11:57.383 --> 11:59.760
♪<i> They silence her voice</i> ♪

11:59.844 --> 12:01.971
♪<i> But I hear her sway</i> ♪

12:02.054 --> 12:07.017
♪<i> Within the sea</i>
<i>of their shame...</i> ♪

12:09.854 --> 12:13.482
♪<i> Fire lady, all you are</i> ♪

12:13.566 --> 12:16.318
{\an5}-(scattered applause)
-♪<i> What you battle</i>
<i>in your heart</i> ♪

12:16.402 --> 12:19.196
♪<i> Has left me scarred</i> ♪

12:21.740 --> 12:23.492
♪<i> In your...</i> ♪

12:23.576 --> 12:25.619
(applause grows louder)

12:27.580 --> 12:29.123
(singing indistinctly)

12:37.339 --> 12:38.549
(whoops)

12:39.592 --> 12:41.552
(laughs):
Whoa, whoa!

12:41.635 --> 12:43.345
Bravo!

12:43.429 --> 12:44.805
Wow!

12:44.889 --> 12:46.557
The ovation tells it like it is!

12:49.768 --> 12:51.937
I've never actually clapped
on this show before ever.

12:52.021 --> 12:55.941
-(laughs)
-That was fantastic.

12:56.025 --> 12:58.319
Jasmine Delancey.

13:00.070 --> 13:01.864
(phone clicking)

13:01.947 --> 13:02.990
(chimes)

13:06.118 --> 13:07.369
(Jasmine chuckles)

13:11.790 --> 13:14.084
<i>JASMINE:</i>
<i>Hi. I'm Jasmine Delancey.</i>

13:17.630 --> 13:19.215
(sighs)
You know,

13:19.298 --> 13:21.884
I first learned how to play
the guitar from my mom.

13:21.967 --> 13:23.886
You know? She taught me
how to play at our lake house

13:23.969 --> 13:26.722
on her old guitar,
which I still have.

13:26.805 --> 13:27.890
(chuckles)

13:27.973 --> 13:30.226
{\an8}And my sister Zara and I would

13:30.309 --> 13:32.561
{\an8}sit by the fire
and make up songs.

13:32.645 --> 13:35.564
<i>When my mom passed away, I was</i>
<i>asked to sing at her funeral.</i>

13:35.648 --> 13:38.567
<i>I sang a song that Zara and I</i>
<i>had wrote for her.</i>

13:38.651 --> 13:41.570
<i>Everyone was looking back</i>
<i>at me, and they weren't crying.</i>

13:41.654 --> 13:43.405
Like my music had stopped them
from crying.

13:43.489 --> 13:46.408
I'll never forget
thinking, "Wow.

13:46.492 --> 13:48.118
(laughs)
I did that."

13:48.202 --> 13:50.079
My music did that.

13:53.707 --> 13:55.834
Hey, Jasmine!

13:55.918 --> 13:57.253
I'm rooting for you.
(whoops)

13:57.336 --> 13:58.712
JASMINE:
Hey, thanks.

13:58.796 --> 14:01.382
{\an5}-Who was that?
-I don't know, it's just...
weird.

14:01.465 --> 14:04.009
(panting)

14:04.093 --> 14:06.887
Oh, wait. Come on.
I need a break.

14:06.971 --> 14:08.264
-ZARA: Are you serious?
-Yeah.

14:08.347 --> 14:10.140
-What...?
-Let me get one of them, man.

14:10.224 --> 14:13.269
-Oh, very heart-healthy.
-You got any cash?

14:14.311 --> 14:16.605
Here you go.

14:16.689 --> 14:18.649
It's on the house. Big fan.

14:18.732 --> 14:19.775
-Of mine?
-Yeah.

14:19.858 --> 14:21.986
I mean, if you feel like
following me on social media...

14:22.069 --> 14:23.904
Hi. Excuse me.

14:23.988 --> 14:25.573
I'm so sorry to bother you.

14:25.656 --> 14:27.449
Can I get a picture?
I'm a huge fan.

14:27.533 --> 14:29.493
(laughs)
Sure.

14:33.372 --> 14:36.292
Perfect. I hope you win.

14:36.375 --> 14:37.626
Thank you.

14:37.710 --> 14:39.753
ZARA:
What is all this?

14:41.338 --> 14:42.840
I sing pretty good.

14:42.923 --> 14:44.592
I... Not that good.

14:44.675 --> 14:46.343
(light applause)

14:49.555 --> 14:50.806
(exhales sharply)

14:53.225 --> 14:54.602
<i>JASMINE:</i>
<i>Zara!</i>

14:57.563 --> 14:59.315
(both laugh)

14:59.398 --> 15:01.984
I mean, she looks pretty great,
doesn't she?

15:02.067 --> 15:04.820
She looks... chilly.

15:04.903 --> 15:07.489
-Hmm?
-Is that the front of the dress?

15:07.573 --> 15:10.659
-Yeah.
-Oh. Okay.

15:10.743 --> 15:12.786
No, it's, um...

15:12.870 --> 15:16.498
It is...<i> blah.</i>

15:16.582 --> 15:18.500
-It's called fashion, Zara.
-No, it just, it doesn't...

15:18.584 --> 15:20.336
It doesn't seem
like your style is all.

15:20.419 --> 15:22.671
You're cool. You should be you.

15:22.755 --> 15:24.590
The hell are you talking about?
I am me.

15:24.673 --> 15:28.344
Imagine if I wore this
to surgery. Right?

15:28.427 --> 15:31.680
Yeah, I'm just saying, like,
you should look like yourself.

15:31.764 --> 15:33.098
I am myself.

15:33.182 --> 15:34.058
Ooh.

15:34.141 --> 15:35.225
I'm Jasmine.

15:35.309 --> 15:37.394
Okay, Jasmine.

15:37.478 --> 15:40.981
You doing one-name status now?
You like Prince or Beyoncé?

15:41.065 --> 15:42.650
{\an8}I just, I mean, look at those.

15:42.733 --> 15:44.151
{\an8}I-I just think
you should wear something

15:44.234 --> 15:45.361
{\an8}that makes you feel comfortable.

15:45.444 --> 15:47.196
{\an8}The hell are you talking
about, Z?

15:47.279 --> 15:50.032
{\an8}Comfortable? I'm not trying
to be comfortable up there.

15:50.115 --> 15:51.700
{\an8}Nobody's comfortable.

15:51.784 --> 15:53.327
{\an8}You're standing
in front of hundreds of people

15:53.410 --> 15:55.371
{\an8}who are just staring at you.

15:55.454 --> 15:57.873
{\an8}Millions more on TV
watching you.

15:57.956 --> 15:59.708
{\an8}(quietly): I'm wasting my breath
trying to explain this to you.

15:59.792 --> 16:02.920
-You're just a doctor.
-I'm <i> just</i> a doctor?

16:03.003 --> 16:05.381
Yeah, you're a doctor.
I'm the artist.

16:05.464 --> 16:07.383
Yeah, I save lives.

16:07.466 --> 16:10.344
-I make life worth living.
-How exactly do you do that?

16:10.427 --> 16:13.055
By singing from my soul.

16:13.138 --> 16:15.683
Cool. Um, well,
that's not only pretentious,

16:15.766 --> 16:18.686
it's also
scientifically impossible.

16:18.769 --> 16:20.312
(sighs)
All right, Jas.

16:20.396 --> 16:24.316
Well, uh, can't wait
to see how far you get

16:24.400 --> 16:26.568
{\an5}-on your meaningless
little singing show here.
-Meaningless?

16:26.652 --> 16:29.488
